Congressman George Miller is retiring after nearly 40 years of representing California in Congress. Throughout his career, he has been dedicated to improving the lives of the middle class. His efforts have resulted in cleaner air and water, better protection for workers' rights, increased access to affordable education, and improved financial stability for working families. Miller played a crucial role in the passage of important legislation, such as the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act and the Affordable Care Act. He has also been a strong advocate for a livable minimum wage. President Obama and First Lady Michelle express their gratitude for Miller's service and leadership and wish him and his family the best in the future.